14/03/2011
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- One of two Greek Cypriots arrested on Saturday (March 12th) for trespassing on a military area in the northern part of the island was released on bail Sunday, pending trial.
Loizos Afxentiou is expected to face a military court Monday.
The second Greek Cypriot, former parliament member Yiannakis Matsis, is in hospital in Famagusta with health issues, and will face a military court once he recovers, local media reported.
Two Polish members of the European Parliament were also detained on Saturday, but were later released.
(CNA, Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet - 13/03/11)
